President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key positions in his administration. Some of the notable appointments include Pam Bondi, Edward McMullen Jr., and Paolo Zampolli as members of the Board of Trustees of the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts. Hope Charlotte Hicks, Derek S. Lyons, and Amy Hanson Swonger have been nominated as members of the J. William Fulbright Foreign Scholarship Board. Richard Grenell and Martin Oliner have been appointed as members of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council. Stephanie Grisham and Jeremy Carl have been nominated as members of the Board of Directors of the National Board for Education Sciences. These are just a few of the appointments mentioned in the article.